docs.abstract: Cranes dot the skyline and construction projects divert traffic as the neighborhood known as DTLA undergoes the biggest development boom since the Roaring Twenties.
docs.snippet: Cranes dot the skyline and construction projects divert traffic as the neighborhood known as DTLA undergoes the biggest development boom since the Roaring Twenties.
docs.lead_paragraph: Los Angeles’s downtown was little more than a sleepy office district not too long ago, where tens of thousands of suburbanites would clear out by the end of the workday and scores of classic Beaux-Arts and Art Deco buildings sat vacant or underutilized.

headline.main: Revitalization Projects Reawaken Downtown Los Angeles
headline.print_headline: A Sleepy Giant, Los Angeles’s Core, Reawakens

docs.abstract: Concern that cars could be seriously hacked — by criminals, terrorists or even rogue governments — has prompted a new round of security efforts on the part of the auto industry.
docs.snippet: Concern that cars could be seriously hacked — by criminals, terrorists or even rogue governments — has prompted a new round of security efforts on the part of the auto industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: Going back at least a decade, cars have been targeted by hackers, some who ended up working with the industry, others acting maliciously. But vehicles now carry far more electronic equipment, and autonomous driving, relying on sensors, cameras and radar, is on the horizon, with all kinds of ripe new targets.

headline.main: Locking More Than the Doors as Cars Become Computers on Wheels
headline.print_headline: Locking Doors Isn’t Enough. Not Even Close.

docs.abstract: At least 20 airlines, primarily in China and Indonesia, grounded the 737 Max 8 plane, and similarities to a recent crash provoked concern among carriers, pilots, flight attendants and passengers.
docs.snippet: At least 20 airlines, primarily in China and Indonesia, grounded the 737 Max 8 plane, and similarities to a recent crash provoked concern among carriers, pilots, flight attendants and passengers.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than a dozen airlines along with the governments of China and Indonesia grounded a new version of Boeing’s most popular jet on Monday, as the American aerospace giant scrambled to deal with the fallout from a deadly plane crash in Ethiopia.

headline.main: Boeing Scrambles to Contain Fallout From Deadly Ethiopia Crash
headline.print_headline: Crisis for Boeing  As Safety Worry Grounds New Jet

docs.abstract: Uber settled a lawsuit with drivers who sought employment status, resolving a longstanding legal issue ahead of its initial public offering.
docs.snippet: Uber settled a lawsuit with drivers who sought employment status, resolving a longstanding legal issue ahead of its initial public offering.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber on Monday settled a long-running legal battle with drivers in California and Massachusetts who wanted the ride-hailing company to recognize them as employees, agreeing to pay the drivers $20 million but not changing their status as independent contractors.

headline.main: Uber Settles Drivers’ Lawsuit for $20 Million
headline.print_headline: Uber to Pay $20 Million To Settle Suit With Drivers
